{"id": "b86d88c821f40a963f7aebd964aca10cff84bd92a0081dcdcb803bdd6b7dd4b2", "item_id": "3496af80ab:0", "text": "A Tessendorf Ocean generator. Code contributed by Amaan Akram ("}
{"id": "f03af51860fdacc8164e92615586cfd8146596868c4794c61b0e0e8b1ddfc76b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:1", "text": "www.amaanakram.com"}
{"id": "6beecfa45e803895ddc848e75c35bd80a03956cbbb866e8c86461eab4aee5a0f", "item_id": "3496af80ab:2", "text": "This produces a bumped normal that can be fed into a displacement shader to create ocean-like waves."}
{"id": "d4055fafa3794fa88b1e89e70c167d5a9575067a1442a6d94e9520d65a575378", "item_id": "3496af80ab:91", "text": "Resolution"}
{"id": "75da1effabe09cb2866f310174d59651812216d0fbbc94c5f3ba7b09295a6644", "item_id": "3496af80ab:5", "text": "Specifies generated texture resolution. Valid settings are 3 through 7. Each value generates the following resolution:"}
{"id": "33847964f7e9478338d5ff2c1662263e2fbf25881ee4f0c200cbcc1971c72288", "item_id": "3496af80ab:6", "text": "A value of 3 generates a resolution of 128x128"}
{"id": "666182541cfbf928a8ee90757529f74fe91a283f9da9c88bd4a04d35903822db", "item_id": "3496af80ab:7", "text": "4: 256x256"}
{"id": "ad5d1979d31585c680d6c327ed9e86552fad6625f211dd806d78cfba1427c161", "item_id": "3496af80ab:8", "text": "5: 512x512"}
{"id": "c00eca261b7f647889ffe9ffa93e80cc8ccf61173721bd7f0c16175069aaad78", "item_id": "3496af80ab:9", "text": "6: 1024x1024"}
{"id": "43743b0f77d51ae51183d5df780f04f0cb9530f3a53453b45e39ed07708607b1", "item_id": "3496af80ab:10", "text": "7: 2048x2048."}
{"id": "d77ce6416bab902c52245642cc03edb6bbd38ef9ac0bdfe0c44c622ab7fe3afe", "item_id": "3496af80ab:11", "text": "Ocean Scale"}
{"id": "bb150552af2b247a4fbb0e0d5189261036735351322016f050ab74081b97096b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:12", "text": "Size of the ocean patch in meters. Larger values \"fit\" a larger expanse of the ocean into the rendered geometry."}
{"id": "367ef06b8fbf3aaaccd9cff1301628fae45901ccd9661b5a1b256c7cc5314d24", "item_id": "3496af80ab:13", "text": "Seed"}
{"id": "85ee09fbc1c1d7648701947489b9365c99b79936d2de535257340f89738daa15", "item_id": "3496af80ab:14", "text": "Seed for the random number generator. Different values produce different ocean patches."}
{"id": "f67e8e66bfee195754d66ce8f0fb67b21663715685729f3c8072e50952c5baf8", "item_id": "3496af80ab:15", "text": "Current Time"}
{"id": "0cdd872c64de8ffa8ada027db9715c144a79e4db400f68d3f9979402f5b80a63", "item_id": "3496af80ab:16", "text": "Current scene time in seconds. Use an expression to drive this parameter."}
{"id": "de6420f54ce074bb8c021a49e09b63742ff6acee68c85f8cd81022ff5e94e8e7", "item_id": "3496af80ab:17", "text": "Repeat Time"}
{"id": "8cf1a92ca5e79d29b16d92ef95c6524f99615bc3186d285bc038e251021ee869", "item_id": "3496af80ab:18", "text": "Waves loop (repeat their shape) after the specified amount of time in seconds."}
{"id": "9efb597c915414fd84e20eedf169e945155c3408df8c13fb82385ca7b96174b7", "item_id": "3496af80ab:19", "text": "Fade"}
{"id": "11dfe02ab7e7eb5ba15eb0d1982a954feb3c9dfdd8fd90b9ae6926abe7fdae7d", "item_id": "3496af80ab:20", "text": "Fades (scales) the ocean vector displacement strength."}
{"id": "092d212313d13e1136ff7a007b0239a098dc331556565d05c2b5aa5290e1e46b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:93", "text": "Chop Amount"}
{"id": "973ccfbb121d61a852c60ee3197b2cb44651e2a91e804513315bd0df401ca761", "item_id": "3496af80ab:22", "text": "The sharpness of the peaks of the waves is controlled by this parameter. Also affects foam values."}
{"id": "8965cdc71634bfb3aee3598d2996bc72c78cbcb1c744076bcd2f9d2368bf0295", "item_id": "3496af80ab:23", "text": "Velocity"}
{"id": "e379cabd060a83587770b931bce3a3f76901e7f190a6aded9960bfffaf4a3098", "item_id": "3496af80ab:24", "text": "Controls the size of the waves. Higher velocities make fewer, but bigger waves. Lower velocities make a calm ocean."}
{"id": "34b7860a343825e6370be5bd721d06226f01b363a26536dc88bcdfc9480a02d6", "item_id": "3496af80ab:25", "text": "Wave Speed"}
{"id": "0519397d61770370965e1fec3398634e64a9256f1922393f96419c08b9c5edaa", "item_id": "3496af80ab:26", "text": "Speed multiplier for waves."}
{"id": "46ade032210498beacdf0811edac41fcfc1dd26137c498d0b335a72dd45b2d8d", "item_id": "3496af80ab:27", "text": "Cutoff"}
{"id": "dddc80d0a2278b668d3f9f8d1f3e61562a4526b1f5e38fbfa315f208f597a28d", "item_id": "3496af80ab:28", "text": "Defines a smoothing factor for the overall ocean surface. Cuts off (removes) waves with wavelengths smaller than the specified value."}
{"id": "ab34b2b0a0037c5704745d6a7d46e6bcba6bdc851263013cd2dbcd62acd49376", "item_id": "3496af80ab:29", "text": "Wave Height"}
{"id": "74bd9c90a1a0c8a82410687eb3719c8389f65be62c8859fe796cbb49207cdfed", "item_id": "3496af80ab:30", "text": "Height multiplier for waves."}
{"id": "fdadeba0ea386a8da0dd3df051aaa0a74b56f8b5146f4ebef3edf42886dc5e1f", "item_id": "3496af80ab:31", "text": "Wind Direction"}
{"id": "0b6cba3f922da0f111c9ea063930c97f2c2a2179f670c40c287e6fbb322dbe16", "item_id": "3496af80ab:32", "text": "The direction the waves travel in."}
{"id": "7667f27a1e58aef0019950d11d816500589af3e514f40711112dc4472cacd4b5", "item_id": "3496af80ab:33", "text": "Damp"}
{"id": "f293acd949859dafa18b6279756f2625019593a235c8677af659a8a09bfd5dab", "item_id": "3496af80ab:34", "text": "Bias waves traveling in the direction of the wind. Value of 0 makes waves travel opposite to the wind direction. 1.0 makes the waves travel in the wind direction only."}
{"id": "a5ae08453630c909abaf134ac4c18b073fd2539b6c8ba2756d410118154d0812", "item_id": "3496af80ab:35", "text": "Wind Align"}
{"id": "c7d7493c8021dae6d6a68f70346fa2be7673bc588a7f9fc86590bbbd8a65e003", "item_id": "3496af80ab:36", "text": "Align waves perpendicular to the direction of the wind, as observed in shallow waters."}
{"id": "ebaca59746d269bf448d9bcd9d1863e688be8ad1fcaad31b0fdba5b460f106af", "item_id": "3496af80ab:37", "text": "Invert Foam"}
{"id": "532b330c4e981f3f67d0171e13018409647fd05176a34ee00700b9900ce0f623", "item_id": "3496af80ab:38", "text": "Makes wave peaks appear white, instead of making wave troughs white."}
{"id": "695462e4082763b2d865074fa09fdebcc6c6476908317a403601227c8b330c05", "item_id": "3496af80ab:40", "text": "Gamma factor to apply to the eigenvalue output."}
{"id": "ec811d30a89ce96d1c7555ffaede78b188fedb1d283adf7cdf55a4edae6697a7", "item_id": "3496af80ab:41", "text": "Brightness"}
{"id": "ec7a99b0f263f4d6329c43bc36d0b259e90aa87e6b5b4d7dc8cd2a1a802ff00c", "item_id": "3496af80ab:42", "text": "Multiplier for the eigenvalues."}
{"id": "427ed16be627e7e8e438785650717fe2c7ce111d831be4bc0350290ef5d3cb6e", "item_id": "3496af80ab:43", "text": "Normalize"}
{"id": "55d5f46710d48241a2e384d633d75eb7208606d99c8ca0071d6dad7ec90e205b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:44", "text": "Whether to normalize the eigenvalues. See"}
{"id": "acaf8b21265484816ee51e67f0df7222b3001b6e2f67916824baebfddfdd52df", "item_id": "3496af80ab:49", "text": "fMin"}
{"id": "16e4e63c405d28acd1d9a24f726ce0a47c6e489e01e8f8a579d65564b5284172", "item_id": "3496af80ab:51", "text": "fMax"}
{"id": "ac31d1c37fdc02a68526addb9ece10ca0e1c5017dc219ed37502941e7b6a356f", "item_id": "3496af80ab:52", "text": "fMin and fMax are used to normalize the eigenvalues, which can go into negative and positive values. See render log for typical values on a frame."}
{"id": "d78cd87c202610475f89d7a32428dded72d579bf3eb2759a2d35ade034f8a628", "item_id": "3496af80ab:53", "text": "Write File"}
{"id": "4a7117c10934ed4518be66741e69159cc5a618e2268e41c11410168162e44aa6", "item_id": "3496af80ab:54", "text": "Writes out a full-float OpenEXR vector displacement map sequence in object space."}
{"id": "45a75c1965cd0b4eff9f0fc2a2945c7ad2fc6cad944713eaac1a6f47762e7abe", "item_id": "3496af80ab:55", "text": "Output Folder"}
{"id": "aa5c0e76cc6831864832baffd9dc3367e8d4fbe4f551efff31c92bb32e4e7a16", "item_id": "3496af80ab:56", "text": "Path to the folder for output images."}
{"id": "54fefc0e45839c212fabbb952ecda21f71e952cf2dd739091bd25c91bcdb8dee", "item_id": "3496af80ab:57", "text": "Postfix"}
{"id": "df9593ecb712ded4030babed1e1e85ec784c61f5215af4fbe45a4332064735ca", "item_id": "3496af80ab:58", "text": "Provides any postfix to apply to the generated file to identify it uniquely."}
{"id": "f9e3e3033c5a1e8a73cd67c0d9e03938441a3c0b07442aab1cce6d6ab404433b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:59", "text": "Current Frame"}
{"id": "6ede83df6cad206a06b90a217399f57c5e03566662fb5a15e3858f7e1d6534a4", "item_id": "3496af80ab:60", "text": "Set an expression for the current frame for frame padded sequence names."}
{"id": "370ba1c7074ca2ae34bd3d908bc380f9053724a7e9853e2b39e6d7e722c7bc69", "item_id": "3496af80ab:61", "text": "Ocean Depth"}
{"id": "52759c4db60c200dcaaad7b9fdc54d58a4318d25c69bc0621352f3b03827e763", "item_id": "3496af80ab:62", "text": "Slows down waves as depth decreases."}
{"id": "b575d5df98d51f80ba1634e2dbb1145ffb2c56c77f0ac79ba1f1c58afe56275b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:63", "text": "Surface Tension"}
{"id": "3bba7e1d2eba7a22620a33820ad50a635e45a01b23b33b657bc6b01be265e9c3", "item_id": "3496af80ab:64", "text": "Capillary waves that run on top of the ocean surface. For small-scale effects only. See the original"}
{"id": "53d1d1273b55010084580837014b8dc5b44dfb5f7f8affeea15677386a0203ef", "item_id": "3496af80ab:65", "text": "Tessendorf"}
{"id": "444e420b1e83bfd0faf102a41c62bfd92f89bf116d1a55aab51a3ddc75e34f1d", "item_id": "3496af80ab:66", "text": "paper for details."}
{"id": "e3109eb112b8b5d6dd25efb433f70bf813e165da8c7f3800a0e999d7ee918b11", "item_id": "3496af80ab:67", "text": "Invert T"}
{"id": "73796e2b41b859e2298597984d1aa5bd182c39cd5cf4c9cd175d7de9cfdeb919", "item_id": "3496af80ab:68", "text": "Inverts the t parameter for the manifold."}
{"id": "e29793dea8429f58cc913ce697117a3614eaa231b5a3942af954b66c44d43850", "item_id": "3496af80ab:69", "text": "Manifold"}
{"id": "e24200ae622d3ccb5e9ad82d22626da57ebc3aeb957b43f54b9d330ece44c407", "item_id": "3496af80ab:70", "text": "Provides the domain over which to apply the displacement. Defaults to s,t."}
{"id": "8b76e2df9050f924b018cff8809cbc580f39a71664984ae54adf99defe9eaa2e", "item_id": "3496af80ab:71", "text": "Output Parameters"}
{"id": "62041492366125427f22f0bc242c2ed9c4d1ee89ced3eec1074ef1093c38942e", "item_id": "3496af80ab:102", "text": "outputDisplacementRGB"}
{"id": "a0cff1de29adcb01a849ee0489d4d936508f384a733425f52237b4f28e65fdcb", "item_id": "3496af80ab:73", "text": "The bumped normal."}
{"id": "5b829770574db252e3c3db8364681adeff7107f1aeb72ba8411a69f6b118b195", "item_id": "3496af80ab:117", "text": "outEigenvalueFloat"}
{"id": "a8346e90f2f99232d93f49d2f00807f59433462fe7c6eadf0fa8732687268b06", "item_id": "3496af80ab:75", "text": "The eigenvalues."}
{"id": "7f1c587d1da4b012edfad8c5de092da9a77721b16baee9e3b6c2ee64fa5e1625", "item_id": "3496af80ab:77", "text": "To quickly get a convincing-looking ocean render, we can use"}
{"id": "eb8180044ec1b869c12616ddd68e7e6a3e27287764b8943f39393a4cf08d3176", "item_id": "3496af80ab:79", "text": "(using the Glass parameters) as the Bxdf. The only thing we want to tweak is the"}
{"id": "2e593b682e2f712b491cc928246fd78104f497c5d2699bb0f7fca81d6b6da406", "item_id": "3496af80ab:81", "text": "(eta), which we'll change to 1.33 to match the value of water."}
{"id": "c89780e5440c7eab88bdc96b5c3bff78369a2282f50f834210617e80b005dc49", "item_id": "3496af80ab:82", "text": "For the displacement, we can use the PxrDisplace shader. Connect aaOceanPrmanShader's"}
{"id": "c730e7b65bd9995da07cf4779c2d3a444ebbff932f1f3e704b2f07cadfb6f847", "item_id": "3496af80ab:84", "text": "output."}
{"id": "0b941dcbf185414915c2e0c99e13092c8e8d596a667259e716589de8f7822c5b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:85", "text": "Below is an example render with the default settings for aaOceanPrmanShader. The ocean is being lit by an environment light using the"}
{"id": "2b020384c2243d9d14f79fef01ef51b39e53f2166611b5ce0538e4753a3d6cc2", "item_id": "3496af80ab:86", "text": "texture that is included with RenderMan."}
{"id": "bb92adaea675508b2549e1d1a9aee2252437c24472e9a6b1b0e366cb396bdb3b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:87", "text": "A calm ocean."}
{"id": "0465ebe1e39c647e36e0de714a3d619c6b5873e124a055b0b504b79a6970cbe5", "item_id": "3496af80ab:88", "text": "Depending on the size of the object, it may be necessary to increase the"}
{"id": "b66081b1e044e13d1d39f2c50a0dcee7285fff3affe1dfeee3b166e05dc4722b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:90", "text": "parameter. For the next render, because of the size of the plane,"}
{"id": "cee555feb3c719f50497312df2bbb37b39d66884c06f8a3845f8f5b314da954e", "item_id": "3496af80ab:92", "text": "has been increased to 7. Also,"}
{"id": "e49e01ac97ca0cc7eec8d7d6e37cbda922e1d78a5ff2f13e1779de740991d138", "item_id": "3496af80ab:94", "text": "is increased to 10.0."}
{"id": "30f3092c638683d08d0a1bdf4a0aa6e27563a68bd8569fb1863ad3db48f8fbd3", "item_id": "3496af80ab:95", "text": "Things are getting bumpy."}
{"id": "fa22d3f27681f72a411d952475aed68c64b6657861168e64a2467e1d5d9d4df5", "item_id": "3496af80ab:96", "text": "To add some simplistic white foam, we can add a diffuse layer to our ocean, by adding diffuse to our"}
{"id": "a2a769e959cfd33c6744a4099fd4d901e8e2814f5dce4ca3f330aece5991d1ef", "item_id": "3496af80ab:99", "text": "Create a"}
{"id": "b7ec5c3dd2824cd278b17988092285709226f237a2256873ff3abf63746e1b5a", "item_id": "3496af80ab:100", "text": "PxrLayerSurface"}
{"id": "79cd0d896776a6956c9ff7322525680d7f492cb15805f748e1b62be22c8c2dde", "item_id": "3496af80ab:101", "text": "shader, and connect the"}
{"id": "c41743d9953dac068e648ce5ee64636401349ac04636c97a88a0343e5c1d2b2d", "item_id": "3496af80ab:103", "text": "output to the (diffuse)"}
{"id": "9db2cebca8713052a7a6dc9c1bb73f05b14eae842eea265c20358544429a3512", "item_id": "3496af80ab:104", "text": "Bump"}
{"id": "84f4c41f84d400d99d6451e949d18d659c0d9e54ddaa9de33ae3a147aeab243e", "item_id": "3496af80ab:105", "text": "parameter and set the (diffuse)"}
{"id": "1ad06f14aabb3a0b10313209523f0121340512c0a14ee61ef579f1930ca3b8b1", "item_id": "3496af80ab:107", "text": "to something closer to white. Make sure that the specular and clear coat lobes have been disabled."}
{"id": "6dd051bc64a9603de90ef47ae23f3fa5a3970ccadfa8ec82208e53e0a34595e4", "item_id": "3496af80ab:108", "text": "For the layer mask, we can use the"}
{"id": "13e295efb0003d47dc5072ee6d6dff582a2add5b0901693b6d4fdb3baf80ddd9", "item_id": "3496af80ab:110", "text": "output from the"}
{"id": "f20ffe2be500904728998fa81c6425dc07e94b57ee6ac4491d2bda673ae57251", "item_id": "3496af80ab:111", "text": "aaOceanPrmanShader"}
{"id": "e7c4959f944b83750c408af0ff5645c1f789bcd1e09485578c4fec2bd23831cd", "item_id": "3496af80ab:112", "text": "pattern. It's necessary that the values fall into the 0-1 range. We can easily enforce that by using a"}
{"id": "36dab77f3fb03bf76601be5d4890330cb021af1ebf3badbd84c1bf9d3f2f621a", "item_id": "3496af80ab:113", "text": "PxrRemap"}
{"id": "d01a05a34d1b90d788c851201c04f21e6527abc9a8401e5aea8ad0eacccc229b", "item_id": "3496af80ab:114", "text": "node. Connect the PxrRemap to the layer mask parameter. Because PxrRemap only works with colors, we can use a"}
{"id": "a15adb89c4d48f8917e8f462340c8868cec431dcf6a128a1e9a49d4e925213b2", "item_id": "3496af80ab:115", "text": "PxrToFloat3"}
{"id": "46edb0985e8b79fa28454108ff5850d1a83ee74683c2ac747465f9f96c6ef4af", "item_id": "3496af80ab:116", "text": "to convert the"}
{"id": "cfd02d335a79056a357de9d9eb56fc293950a3ec38f979d33b97574efff2e2d4", "item_id": "3496af80ab:118", "text": "to a triplet. Set the"}
{"id": "0ea3fb79b4e60d79419689efc3cf409c1dd4977a16280e0d415e56414c05d93c", "item_id": "3496af80ab:119", "text": "Input Min"}
{"id": "5f2baf150943ca0c79809807ce8ee5025e3e52defd023ce995d279cba8297855", "item_id": "3496af80ab:121", "text": "Input Max"}
{"id": "db11b3905397e50c19b2615e9d58def847d3551077d918be3f22ea426372fb59", "item_id": "3496af80ab:122", "text": "to -5 and 5, respectively, on the PxrRemap node."}
{"id": "b5322a2e133a0f62346b333e37adeac260deb3aab726bc564dcc3f7d2d8d07ef", "item_id": "3496af80ab:123", "text": "Lastly, turn on"}
{"id": "79f88a4a72bd6f95d18375cb27fa0b3af8c7bf35598daca13d064ebd394347ae", "item_id": "3496af80ab:124", "text": "invertFoam"}
{"id": "1fb08409e43aee447d535b39cbeb20e27621a9cd162a52c7597398f1a1c56fb8", "item_id": "3496af80ab:125", "text": "in the aaOceanPrmanShader node so that the white appears at the wave peaks. You should then get a render similar to the image below."}
{"id": "5d4665bab1f58cc437e60c315913ad663cf9b121bc4067a2217289e88d5e169f", "item_id": "3496af80ab:126", "text": "Not so calm anymore."}
